<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,150,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,538,186,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Crowell, R. M." box="[911,1085,187,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" pagination="265 - 270" refId="ref15456" refString="Crowell, R. M. (1990) Unionicola billieaehonore, new species, a sponge-associated Hydracarina (Acari: Unionicolidae) from New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 17 (2), 265 - 270. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1990.10422601" type="journal article" year="1990">Crowell (1990)</bibRefCitation>
as developmentally associated with freshwater sponges in the Northern Hemisphere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,150,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species belongs to the ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[593,731,259,284]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Unionicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis box="[593,731,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">U. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—complex’ of sponge-mite. This species was reported in 
<collectingRegion country="Iran" name="Gilan" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Gilan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[311,356,295,321]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hevers, J." box="[370,518,295,321]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" pagination="265 - 280" refId="ref16786" refString="Hevers, J. (1984) Die Unionicola crassipes-Gruppe in Japan und in Iran. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 31 (4 - 5), 265 - 280." type="journal article" year="1984">Hevers 1984</bibRefCitation>
). It needs further study (emphasizing on developmental study) of this mite to get a better idea about association with freshwater sponges.
</paragraph>
